          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Mr. Leeser</addressee>
                                        <add>Hebrew</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Hebrew</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>Rev <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi>
                                        </add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                                        <date>Friday, Pericosse Behar,</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><date>(May), 1849</date>.</p>
                              <p>Rev. Mr. Leeser:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">By express I received <add>back</add> this morning
                                        the<lb/> Torah, and just now I received your letter.
                                        “Since<lb/> *I would rather give it to you than to another
                                        man”,<lb/> I take this opportunity, <del>to</del> since
                                        another one presents<lb/> itself for sale, at the price of
                                        $80. to offer you this one<lb/> at a reduction of $5, namely
                                        at $85. It is certainly<lb/> worth more, although the other
                                        one is also a handsome<lb/> Torah and also belongs to me. If
                                        you want it, I shall<lb/> see that it is transferred to you.
                                        The other party is not<lb/> particularly to give it on
                                        commission. For my own, I<lb/> have a buyer. I am convinced
                                        that I could get<lb/> more for it, nevertheless, 'first
                                        come, first served,'<lb/> I am awaiting your answer.
                                        Greetings from my<lb/> dear wife, who, with God's help, will
                                        soon recover.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Respectfully,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Schnaor<add>?</add>
                                        <persName role="author">Nussbaum</persName></p>
                              <p>*Genesis 29.19</p>
                    </body>
